content.message: Hello. Do you play any video games?
I do play games.  I enjoy the call of duty game series.
I also enjoy that game. Did you know video games were initially called cathode ray tube amusement devices and were used by the military?
Yes, cathode ray tubes have come and gone and the game plays on.  I have a Playstation 3, but no plans to upgrade.
I have a ps3 as well. I dont see the point to buying a ps4. This one is all I need as well.

The game Destiny turned me off gaming.  It was fun to play, but it demands network connectivity.  Sometimes the old games are just fun.  Donkey Kong and Mario are still OK.  I see Fifa 14 works on PS2, PS3 and PS4.
I was never into soccer games. I liked Madden though. Did you know that ps3s are being used to research black holes.
Yes, people let them run and they network together.  Sort of like the 1760 PS3's used by the department of defense to make a super computer.  Never tried Madden.
Never played madden. You will have to try it. How about grand theft auto. Have you played that one?
I do indeed love GTA.  I want to say that I played early rev levels on a PC.  It was a different game back then. FUDGE RIPPLE!  I will search for a disk and see if it is audio.
THe original game when played in a cd player would play the soundtrack to the game.
Interesting.  Have you ever had carpel tunnel syndrome brought on by playing games?
Actually I have. I dont know if that is why I got it though. I was typing a lot for work when I got it.
Yes, it can be a big deal.  Imagine a Major League Baseball player missing games because of carpel tunnel.  LOL.
I can imagine it. It really is painful. Did you know that baseball managers wear a uniform because they are allowed to play if needed?
Haha.  Imagine if your boss could sit in for you at work.  He would be steamed if you said, "I have a Fortnite related injury and must sit this out."
He would be steamed and I would be totally embarrassed. Lol. Did you ever play soccer baseball. That's what Canadians call kickball.
Kickball on the playground. What fun.  David Price is the MLB player with a 217 million dollar seven year contract.  Cant play ball games.  Perhaps because of video games. He might try kick ball.
Maybe he should. What did you think about that guy findin 3 million dollars worth of old baseball cards in his grandpas attic.
Finding 3 million dollars worth is like finding an unlock code for life.
It wouldn't guarantee you win the game but it would sure make it a lot easier. Lol. Have a great day.
Have a good day.
Hey there Hoss and do you watch TV? I usually watch TV or Netflix
Hello there, yeah me too, plenty of tv for me. I like watching shows like Simpsons
Yeah I like The Simpsons a lot. Have you seen the episode where Bart does not appear? I hear that he doesn't show his face and he isn't even mentioned
I have not seen that one but I am really curious about it. Do you ever watch the SNL?
Yes I've seen SNL before. What about you? I can't say it's my favorite but I like the old ones, like in the 90s with Adam Sandler, what about you?
Yeah I used to watch it too but not so much anymore. Apparently the Weekend Update is the longest running skin in it
Oh wow that's interesting. I do like that segment, I bet they had that since the first episode. Do you ever watch South Park though?
Only sometimes. In the SImpsons though, Homer held as many as 188 episodes in just the first 400 episodes

That's incredible, imagine if that were like real life LOL! You would definitely have to write a book about all those jobs. did you know that the creators of The Simpsons sent the creators of South Park some flowers? Do you know why they did that
I wonder if that was ironic in any way or just for wrapping up things. How about plays, do you ever watch them?
No I don't really watch any place to be honest with you. Just TV mostly. I do like that show That 70s Show though, have you seen that?
I have seen it actually a few times. I also watch plays sometimes but did not know that all but one of Shakespeare's works have been turned into plays
That is interesting. I do like Shakespeare one of his best Works was the movie Titus by the way, have you seen that movie?
I am not sure if I have seen that one. How about Shark Tank, do you ever watch that?
I have seen shark tank before. Do you like that show? I heard that most of those deals were fake, what do you think
I have only seen it a few times and now that you are mentioning this fact I think it was a good decision from me to stop watching it, so fake
Yeah I agree with you. I'd rather watch Thomas the Tank Engine it's probably a lot more realistic LOL did you know that they had a lot of famous narrators on that show
Oh that is cool. Was Daniel Radcliffe one of them? I know he did the voice of Edward Cullen on the Simpsons parody
No I don't think he was, but some other guys that were were Alec Baldwin, George Carlin, and Ringo Starr. I love George Carlin so I might watch some old episodes for him
Oh that is a cool cast for sure. Back to Netflix, do you know how they decide in European market what shows to purchase?
No I don't what do they do? On a different topic, how often do you wear shoes? I know that I wear shoes almost every day unless I'm being lazy LOL
Hello.  Do you play piano?
No I wish, I tried though.
What topics are you interested in discussing?
Piano is fine.  Did you know there was an aluminum grand piano?
Yes, I heard one that was built for the lounge of the airship Hindenburg that weighed only 356 pounds. That was very light for a grand piano.
Seems like it would slide around on the airship then lol.
Yes, I would think so. I also enjoy piano concerts. Do you like live music performances?
Love them.  I like band Concerts mostly.  You?
I went to see a piano concert by John Legend in the past.  Yes, I enjoy good piano concerts.
Lucky!  I bet he would sound good in an acient roman amphitheater
I think so.  In Croatia, there is an ancient roman amphitheater that is still being used as a concert venue.
Do you think they would let creed play there?
I am sure as long as they are willing to pay.  Creed had a concert that was so bad that people filed a lawsuit against them.
I guess you are right, pink floyd played there with no audience!
I heard that they did that in 1972.  I wonder why they did not want to have no audience.
I dont know.  Linkin park did 324 concerts in 2001
That was a lot in one year! I think it had to do with the success of their first album.
Yes.  The ramones played 2263 though!
That was a lot!  Was it within a year though?
lol ,no it was over 20 years!
Linkin Park did 324 in one year - Ramones probably did less on a yearly basis.
That is almost one daily, crazy.  Take care and nice chat
It was nice chatting with you too. Have a nice weekend!
I enjoy the NFL. Are you a fan?
I watch them because my son is a big fan and the entire family enjoy NFL games.
Glad to hear it. Out of the 32 teams which one is your family rooting for? I'm a Bears fan myself.
The 49ers from San Francisco because we used to live there.
That makes sense. Are you familiar with the former Patriots RB Benjarvus Green-Ellis?
Yes.  I heard that he has never fumbled the ball in his NFL career.
Yes. That is so impressive. I did not know that was possible! Did you ever hear what the University of Iowa did to their visiting locker room?
Yes.  They painted the locker room for visiting teams pink.  To intimidate them?
Yes they did. I'm assuming it's some kind of mind game.
I think so.  What do you think of Tom Brady?
I'm not a fan. How about yourself?
I admire him for winning five championship.  Four or five?  I do not remember.
I do not even know at this point. It's a lot. I definitely think he is a very good QB. Did you hear that he wrote a book?
No I did not.  Please tell me about it.
He wrote a book called The TB12 Method. It's referred to as an Athlete's Bible.
What kind of book is it?
I suppose it depends on who you ask. I believe that he believes it's spiritual but a critic called it cult like and creepy.
What do you think though?
I have not read it so I truly can't make that judgement. Off topic, did you know that ESPN won an Emmy for creating the yellow line that represents the first down?
Yes I heard about it.  The yellow line was a good idea for American football.
It was an amazing idea. I can't imagine watching without it. I would get completely lost. They deserved that Emmy.
Yes, they did indeed.  Did you watch the superbowl this year?
I did. It was horrible in every way ha ha.
Hi, do you like football?
Hi, I love football. What about you?
I do love football. My favorite team is the Chicago Bears. Do you have a favorite team?
I love the Cincinnati Bengals. Did you know the NFL has no written rule against females playing?
I did not. Wow. The avg game is only 11 minutes!
That's crazy. I guess most of the time is spent in the huddle?
Yeah. Do you know where the huddle originated from?
I saw it was from a deaf QB. Makes sense so the other team can't see your plays.
Yeah. Saint cheerleaders are not allowed to dine in the same restaurant as players.
Interesting...I think I've heard many other teams have similar rules like that between the players and the cheerleaders.
I feel like that is a little parochial. Why can't they hang out?
I agree. Did you know the NFL uses tracking chips embedded in player pads?
I did not know that. I do love chips though, especially Doritos!
haha. They use the chips to track ball speed, velocity, location, and rotation.
Oh, I use chips to get fatter... so basically the same thing. Do you like the patriots?
HAHAHA! No I don't like the Patriots. Do you?
I do not really. I am a bears fan. Do you have a favorite team?
I love the Bengals. Do you like Tom Brady?
He's ok. I want to hate his persona but everyone that has met him, likes him. So I am not sure. Yu?
Not a huge fan. His wife actually makes more money than he does. They are very rich.
I'd say so! It was nice chatting with you!
Good evening! What do you think of snakes? I think they are fascinating being ectothermic and covered in scales!
Yes I agree there with you. DId you know some owls keep blind snakes in their nests?
That is fascinating but why? Some legless lizards look just like snakes but they have eyelids and external ears!
THey keep them there because they reduce the number of parasites in the nest
Oh I see. very smart indeed. Speaking of snakes in high places, there is a genus of flying snakes that launch themselves at prey!
Wow that must look scary. Did you know Australia has the most venomous snakes?
Yes I have been there many times. Over in New Zealand though...no snakes!
That sounds like a peaceful place. Did you know that not all snakes lay eggs?
Agreed. I thought they all did. One thing I did know is that their organs are one in front of the other not side by side like ours.
Cool fact. The ones that are born with two heard fight with each other for food
Two heads? Sounds like a horror film lol. Fear of snakes is common in animals, not just humans but monkeys too.
I know right? There is a guy that has been bitten so much by them that his blood now is used as antivenom
Whoa he must be very tough. Although crocodiles look like snakes they are more closely related to birds if you can believe it!
Wow that sounds a little off but cool. Do you use facebook much?
Not as much as I used to. I used it more back in 2012 when it was valued at 104 billion dollars! You?
Yeah me too.Did you know it is mentioned in a third of the divorce filings?
Nope but I believe it! People are crazy! Mark Zuckerburg suffered red-green colorblindness so he made facebook's color blue!
That is convenient for him. A third of people in the US get their news from there
Wow that is scary. Burger King had a promotion where if you unfriended 10 people you would get a free whopper. Would you? It was great chatting with you tonight!
Same here and hope you have a great one
Alright thanks bye!
Hello, are you a Thor fan?
Oh, I'm a big fan of all the Marvel films!  How about yourself?
I like them all too but i prefer Thor myself
I thought Thor Ragnarok was the best of the Thor films.  I think it might be in part because of all the improvised dialogue.
Yeah me too, that surely made it more realistic in nature
Did you know Tom Hiddleston originally tried out for the part of Thor?  He even went on a strict diet and gain 50 pounds of muscle.
wow, that sucks that he did all that just to be a side kick
Ahhh, but he makes such a good Loki though!  It's like one of Marvel's most memorable villains!
yeah but i'm sure he was depressed about the change in character
You remember that mid credits scene in the Avengers where they're all at that Shawarma restaurant?  They say that caused a noticeable increase in sales.  I find that pretty funny
Oh yeah, i'm sure the restaurant was glad of that free advertisement!
Like Tony, I'd never even HEARD of Shawarma before seeing that movie!  (Still haven't had a chance to try it though..)
Yeah, its a small restaurant in LA

I bet Sony is kicking themselves for not having bought the rights to ALL Marvel characters way back when they had the chance.  (Course, this was long before superhero films had become big business...)
Yeah, i know i would be. You would think that they would think of the future as far as comic characters go and realize that they all would eventually be big names!
Did yo know Marvel once created a superhero with a hearing aid just for a boy who had to wear them?
That is awesome, I'm sure the boy wears them now
Yeah, they called him Blue Ear, and the boy was 4 years old at the time.
That is so cool
Another weird little factoid.. the guy who voices Jarvis in the Iron Man films has never actually SEEN the films.  Thought that was kind of weird..
Yeah, that IS weird! Well, it was great chatting with you. I hope you have a great day, take care!
Hello there, are you a fan of jazz music?
Like some jazz. Find Coltrane a bit hard to listen to for long, but enjoyed the Alvin Ailey dance company's portrayal of his jazz in movement to be inspiring.
It is a bit hard to listen to very long, unless you are really into jazz in my opinion.  I do enjoy some myself.

Agreed. Dance, for me, isn't hard to watch for very long. Have always loved broadcasts of Ailey's dancers, Twyla Tharp's company years ago, and the NY City Ballet. What athletes and magicians dancers can be. But the companies can also be tough places to earn a fair living.
That is very true, I think it requires just as much skill and training as any professional sport.
I'm sure you're right. Artists are not often, by nature, "tough" negotiators, but things are changing. Dance companies, like orchestras today, have unions, stage boycotts, and threaten strikes.
That is true as well.  Did you know that Tupac used to dance ballet in high school?
I can see him, portraying the Mouse King in the Nutcracker. Bet he enjoyed a villain role, since they're usually deliciously villainous!
I bet he did!  That would be fun to see an old video of him performing that role.

Agreed. I'd also like to see the late Bruce Lee, who was a great dancer. So many activities, from martial arts to figure skating to marching bands can include dance-like movements or qualities. Athletics, of course, also inspires sometimes like dance movement.
I bet he was an excellent dancer, he could move around effortlessly it seemed.  And I agree, all types of athletics.

Take Tom Brady, Patriots long-time QB for example. Sometimes when he makes an accurate throw, his movement syncs with the ball, which flies magically right to a receiver, and the receiver's leap is just like a dance movement.
That is an excellent example!  Did you know that ballet dancers can go through 4 pairs of shoes in a single week!?

Heard that, and I believe it. Think that refers to classical ballet dancers, not necessarily modern dance. Alvin Ailey pioneered modern dance, and he understood that audiences want to see more athleticism, like they'd see on a field, court or in a stadium.
I think you are right about that.  It just shows you how much wear and tear that has on those feet.

Feet that bleed a lot, like those of gymnasts and countless other athletes. I admire the courage it takes to endure, in the arts or in athletics. Did you know that the 88 year old actor and director, Clint Eastwood, is a lifelong fan of jazz - and he plays piano, and even created the score for his Oscar-winning film, Million Dollar Baby. Who knew?
That is impressive, he is a very talented person, I can't believe he still kicks so much butt at his age.
Must be in the genes. Maybe athletes and other performers have just a bit of bird DNA still kicking around their gene pool. Avian magic. Who knows?
Oh I think genes plays a huge role in that.  In anything really, those that really make it, usually have a relative that was into the same type of thing.
True. Did you know that the vast majority of bird species are monogamous, some just for one breeding season, others for years or even for life. From penguins to cardinals...
No I didn't know that, but very interesting.  Well it's been nice chatting, I hope you have a nice day!
Hello. Do you watch sports much?
I do! I like basketball, though I was never very good as a kid as I'm not very tall. How about you?
I played a little in school but I was never as great as some of these pro players. There are some great players out in the various leagues.
Oh yeah. Kareem Abdul-Jabbar used to be so great at the dunk, it was banned from college basketball.
Wow I can't imagine the game without the dunk now. It such an iconic move. I wonder why more people don't do the 3 pointers to rack up the score though.
It's much easier to get blocked from back there, I suppose. Dunking allows more control over the ball.
I guess that makes sense. I always just assumed there was only a 3pointer, a layup and a dunk but I guess there is also something called a field goal that is worth two points.
I believe a field goal is just any shot that's not a free throw, as all other shots are two or three points. Free throws are one point.

It has been so many years since I played that I had forgotten all of that. I bet I could still hustle a game at the supreme court basketball court though.  I can't imagine the justices have many hoop skills.
Yeah, I love that they call it "the highest court in the land".
Leave it to the government to try and be all "punny". I wonder if they have their own coach. If they do that guy probably makes bank.
I wonder if they even play on a team so organized like that, or if they just have pick up games. Have you ever heard of James Naismith?
He invented the game right?
He did, and he was the only losing coach in KU's history! That's an unfortunate twist of fate.
Can you imagine the humiliation of being bad at your own game? That would be like Hugh Laurie being a horrible drama teacher despite his acting success.
I love Hugh Laurie. A lot of people don't realize he's British because he uses an American accent on House. Did you know he was the highest paid tv drama actor for a time?
Yeah he deserved every penny too. His acting was suberb in that. I was shocked the first time I heard him speak. I have no idea he was british.
You know who else is good who actually taught drama? Jon Hamm.
Yeah he was a fantastic teacher. He actually taught one of the girls from the show the office, Ellie Kemper.
Yeah, I remember hearing that. It's funny because he's in the show Unbreakable Kimmie Schmidt with her.
That is really funny. Well it has been nice chatting with you. Have  a great evening.
Likewise!
Do you watch a lot of television?
Hi! I watch some tv how about you?
I watch a lot of netflix and amazon Prime, so I guess that counts lol. Did you know there are over 750 episodes of pokemon? 50 a year for 16 years straight.
Wow, that is a lot of tv episodes! Sometimes my room mate watches Golf on TV, haha, very uneventful. I just listen to my albums I have downloaded on my phone haha
Man i feel you on that, I hate golf, has to be the most boring sport ever created. Do you like Linkin Park?
I know Golf is the worst even though there are so many Golf courses in the US they take up more land space than Rhode Island and Delaware haha very popular! But on TV wow sooo slow.
Yeah and there is a golf course in Dubai that requires 4 million gallons of water a day, seems like such a huge waste of water.

Wow! These Golf courses require a lot of care! And yes, I love Linkin Park! I have all of their albums on my phone and if given the chance watch them on Youtube on my TV....So sad Chester passed away.
Yeah it just goes to show no matter how much money you have, it is not a substitute for happiness. i doubt we hear any more music from them, at least not for a long time.
Even if we do hear any more music it will never be the same. But their albums will be here forever.
Yep same as Nirvana, i still listen to them pretty often, and the with streaming services it is easier than ever to listen to whatever you want from any age.

Very true. I love Nirvana as well. I could just listen to music all day everyday instead of watching TV and be fine with it lol. One of my all time fav old albums is Dark side of the Moon. it was released over 40 years ago and still one of the best selling albums.
Nwa's album Straight Outta Compton was the first album to reach platinum status without airplay or a major tour, to bad they did not last long. The movie is pretty solid to.
Definitely, I agree. I watched The movie on TV and really liked it. The album is awesome! So do you have a favorite TV show?
I like Game of Thrones, but I feel like that might be a lot of peoples answer haha, if I am bored I like to re watch episodes of Thats 70s show on Netflix though.
haha, I love that 70's show too, And actually I am one of the few people who has never watched one episode of Game of Thrones lol I don't know why, just haven't.

Well I read the A song of fire and ice books before the show was ever a thing and I loved them, though the show is quite a bit different from the books. I am still waiting for The Expanse to start on amazon.
Oh, cool. I usually like reading the books prior to watching them on TV or going to the movies. It's always different!
Yeah I read a lot, it's probably one of my main past times when I get bored or just have free time to myself.
Me too. I have a huge collection of books from throughout my life and even picked up some that I don't remember buying lol. Better than TV anyday, but I love my album collection too.
Yeah I am trying to get my nephews more into reading and not so much having screens in front of their faces 24/7. Anyway it was a good chat. Have a good day.
Hello, do you watch  the NFL?
Every week. How about yo.
Nice. I watch it sometimes only. Do you know how many teams are there?
Yeah there are 32 teams arent there
Yup there are. Did you know U of Iowan painted their visitor locker room pink?
I did know that. I doubt it really had any effect on the other team though. What do you think about that.
Yeah it does not seem to have much effect either. Bowlers used to make more than football players in the 60s, wow
Yeah I would say that average players make a whole lot more today than the stars did back then. Crazy how much money is in football.
That is true and yet engineers make more over their lifetime
I heard that. Did you know that espn actually won an emmy for the yellow line they superimpose on the screen to show the first down
Yeah that is strange but good for them, I guess it helps a lot with watching the game
It does give us fans a better perspective of how far they need to get for a first down. If you think about it. Its pretty simple but genius.
Yeah for sure. Do you know what the highest score is in history of football?
YeIn 1916 georgia tech beat cumberland 222-0. Bet they didnt want to play them again for awhile, huh.
I bet so too. Georgia Tech must be still bragging to this day about that amazing win.
Everything would have to go perfect every play to sore that many points. Usually when a team gets up by so much they let off a little bit. They sure didnt on that day.
Yeah exactly. Did you hear they are using tracking chips on the players now?
Yeah they are in their shoulder pads I believe. They are also placed inside the footballs
Yeah, they are tracking velocity and rotation so I have they can use that data to make the game safer too
Lets hope so. Its cool all the information they can get these days.
I know so much out there. It was nice chatting with you.
Hi, how are you?
I am good, you? Lets talk about congress, there has been only 1 non human to testify in front of congress and that is Elmo
Wow, I wonder what Elmo had to testify to congress about?
I dont know, the first women was elected to congress in 1916
Yeah, I heard that happened even before she had the right to vote in a national election.
just like fantasy football, there is a fantasy congress also
That's interesting.  I hear players draft member of congress and get points for their successes with legislation.
There is also a baseball game that both sides play each year, so far the republicans are leading by 3 wins
Cool, I'm a Republican,go team!  Not to change the subject or anything, but did you hear about the man in France that sold the Eiffel tower not once but twice?
i have not, the government owns a lot of land in Nevada, 86% of it.
Makes you wonder what they are doing with so much land in Nevada?  It's basically all dry desert out there.
The Norwegian government cares about the amazon rain forest, donating 1bn in 2008
That was very nice of them to do that.  I wish there were more people like that in this world. I love the Amazon rainforest, it's beautiful.
there is a law that passed in 2006 that protects governments employees who violate the Geneva convention.
I haven't heard about that law, yet.  Did you know that Wikileaks published the government's plans to destroy It?
no, lets talk about the president next. I wonder how much time the president spends in the guest house, its bigger then the white house
Probably not a lot, I think he's always traveling.  Do you know who the top 3 wealthiest US presidents were?
I know Washington was one of the top three in history so far.
JFK and Jefferson were the other two of the top 3.
that might need to be updated because Trump is the wealthiest we have ever had.
I agree with you about that! Well, it's been nice chatting with you this morning.  I hope you enjoy the rest of your day.
Do you pay attention to the NFL playoffs at all?
Yes I do.
Which of the teams were you rooting for this year? I watched a few of the games, and there was a lot of potential in a lot of the teams that makes me want to keep my eye out for them next season
I thought the Rams were a good contender and also the Kansas City Chiefs.  I think it all boils down to what quarterback has a good passer rating.
True! It definitely would have been interesting had it been the Chiefs against the Rams. The QB is key in those games though
I know what you mean. Take Andrew Luck for example.  He's the quarterback for the Colts and he's the 10th most valuable passer of the year.
I wonder if the fact that Kellan Moore is the only lefty NFL QB affects how the team has been doing the past few years
Could be, then again perhaps not.  There has been a deaf quarterback back in the day. He's the whole reason the teams get into huddles.
I wonder how well that team did overall. He seems like the kind of guy who could adjust well to the circumstances around him
Yes he does and the team with him. They figured out that by huddling they could keep opponents from reading his hand signals.
Some football players are smart like that. For instance, Alex Smith was working on his master's degree by the time he was in the NFL draft because he started college as a junior
He started college as a junior?  I guess he was really working in high school not just on football but on education too.
I guess if you take all the AP classes while in high school, college can be shortened by two years. He must have been a good player too to be the first overall pick in 2005
Speaking of good players, have you heard of baker mayfield?  Not only is he a great quarterback but also a great gamer.  He thought about going professional on video game competitions.
Football probably pays more though, and gaming is a good Plan B if the NFL route doesn't work out
That's true.  Football pays good now but in the 1960s bowlers made more than players.

Do professional bowlers still make money nowadays? It seems that ESPN has changed the popularity of football, especially with that first down line they invented that made it easier to viewers to keep track of the game
It definitely does. I think it adds to the excitement too because you know just how far they have to go to get their first down.
It was a good enough invention to win an Emmy. Sometimes it's the simple things that make a difference
That's true lol!  Do you watch any college football?  They had the highest scoring game ever.
I don't, but wasn't it back when Georgia Tech played Cumberland in 1916?
It was, georgia tech scored 222 unanswered points!
I feel bad for the guys on Cumberland's team. At some point they must have given up
do you watch the Game of Thrones?
I have no idea but the great great great grandson of Dickens plays in it
I see. I have only seen some episodes and noticed that , his name is Harry Lloyd
Yeah and Also Charlie Chaplins granddaughter is in it as well
Yea if I remember correctly she plays the role of Talisa Maegyr
Yes. DId you know the name Arya is being given to lots of kids now?
Yes and in part is thanks to the name in GoT
Yeah. Did you know they are financed by Ireland in part?
Yes that is because it has really helped with their tourism as parts of it are filmed there
Makes sense. Did you hear of that show called Game of Lions?
Yes that is in Nat Geo, so cool. Do you like cars?
I love cars actually. Do you know who invented the drive thru?
That was McDonald's back in 1975, it has been a while
Yeah and do you know why that idea came about?
Yes the soldiers were not allowed out of the cars in fatigues
Yeah that was nice to accommodate them. Do you know why the trunk of the car is called that?
It is because the old cars used to have wooden trunks
Yes. Do you know how cadillac got its name?
Yes after the founder of Detroit, de la Mothe Cadillac
Yes that is very fitting. Nice chatting with you
Same here , have a good one
Are you a Lady Gaga fan?
Yes, musically and as an actress. I just heard a new extended version of a star is born is coming out. I can't wait to see the extra footage.
I have not seen it at all but I am interested. It got a lot of acclaim. Do you know that Lady Gaga is the godmother of Elton John's son?
Yes, shes tweeted about him a lot. You should follow her on twitter she has well over 11 million followers and posts all kinds of neat stuff.
I just recently followed her so I missed a lot. Speaking of, did you also know that the LAPD asked her to tweet her followers about some upcoming roadwork?
I guess they have a lot less followers. Smart idea! She's come a long way since she was on boiling points.
I forgot that show existed. I had no idea she was on that. I'm sure she's a bit embarrassed about that now.
Maybe, you know it's funny I love her music but she's not really what I'd consider typical to what I listen to. Then I find out her favorite band is Iron Maiden and it makes sense.
I didn't know about that either. I usually prefer rock as well but I'm not against some catchy pop here and there to get my day going or to work out to. It has it's place for sure.
I just wish she'd tour more. I have seen a few of her concerts but there are not that many opportunties.
You would think she would since that's a lot of the income for singers now. Do you enjoy going to concerts?
